goals.rationale: This helps to identify the range of lengths of airport names and can be useful for airlines to choose appropriate names for their new airports.

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    country_counts = data['country'].value_counts()
    country_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of airports by country?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
```
```python
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['latitude'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Airports')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
```
```python
    data['name_length'] = data['name'].apply(lambda x: len(x))
    plt.hist(data['name_length'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Length of Airport Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names by length?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
